[^TEXT: THE TRIALL, OF LIEUT. COLLONELL JOHN LILBURNE, BY AN 
EXTRAORDINARY OR SPECIAL COMMISSION, OF OYEAR AND TERMINER AT THE
GUILD-HALL OF LONDON, THE 24, 25, 26. OF OCTOB. 1649.
BEING AS EXACTLY PEN'D AND TAKEN IN SHORT HAND, AS IT WAS POSSIBLE TO
BE DONE IN SUCH A CROUD AND NOYES, AND TRANSCRIBED WITH AN INDIFFERENT
AND EVEN HAND, BOTH IN REFERENCE TO THE COURT, AND THE PRISONER; (...)
PUBLISHED BY THEODORUS VARAX.
(...)
PRINTED BY HEN. HILS IN ST. THOMAS'S SOUTHWARK.
(1649).
